name: Monte Xanic
description: Pioneer winery founded 1987. Grand Gold Medal winner. Family-friendly with mini zoo.

name: L.A. Cetto
description: Founded 1928. Largest and oldest winery in Mexico. Nebbiolo specialist.

name: El Cielo
description: Most awarded Mexican winery 8 consecutive years. Luxury resort with lake views.

name: Finca la Carrodilla
description: First certified organic and biodynamic winery. Rooftop tastings.

name: Bodegas Magoni
description: 50+ years. Famous 400-500 year old oak tree. Traditional methods.

name: Adobe Guadalupe
description: Luxury winery and inn. Horseback vineyard tours. Spanish tapas food truck.

name: Viñedos de la Reina
description: World award-winning wines. Damiana Michelin Star restaurant on site.

name: Santo Tomás
description: First female winemaker Laura Zamora. Villa Torél Bib Gourmand restaurant.

name: Vena Cava
description: Built from reclaimed fishing boats! Natural wines. Troika food truck with octopus tostadas.

name: Hacienda la Lomita
description: Organic viticulture. Lunario Michelin Star + Green Star restaurant.

name: Bruma Wine Resort
description: Architecture icon. Casa Ocho Best Boutique Hotel Mexico. Fauna restaurant.

name: Decantos Vinícola
description: Iconic semicircular façade. Panoramic views. Most affordable Valle option.

name: Las Nubes
description: The Clouds hilltop location. Breathtaking panoramic views. Pet-friendly.

name: Cieli
description: Opposite hillside sunset views. Friendly cats and rescued dogs. Meet winemaker.

name: Don Tomás
description: Luxury cabanas for overnight stays. Steaks and cheese boards.

name: Casa Magoni
description: Hidden gem. Relaxed scenic atmosphere. Affordable tasting.

name: Primitivo
description: 300-year oak tree. Fire pit cooking. Chef Carolina Jiménez. Michelin Recommended.

name: Casa de Piedra
description: Sparkling wine specialist. Collaboration with Conchas de Piedra restaurant.

name: Hacienda Guadalupe Vinícola
description: Historic hacienda architecture. Traditional Mexican winemaking.

name: Villa Montefiori
description: Camillo Magoni family. Italian flair. Cozy intimate setting.

name: Lechuza Vineyard
description: Miller family boutique. Award-winning reds. Intimate experience.

name: Vinos Pijoan
description: Pau Pijoan honest wines. Home-like patio. Rescue dogs greet visitors.

name: Xecue
description: Modern relaxed atmosphere. Pet-friendly. Affordable tastings.

name: Tres Mujeres
description: Women-owned winery. Female winemakers. Empowerment focus.

name: Alximia
description: Experimental natural wines. Funky artistic approach.

name: Vinícola Toyan
description: Family heritage winery. Traditional methods passed down generations.

name: Casa Frida
description: Large-scale operation. Party atmosphere. Controversial but popular.

name: Cavas Sol y Barro
description: Sun and Clay. Rustic earth-focused. Clay barrel cellars.

name: Museo de la Vid y el Vino
description: Wine museum. Educational tours. History of region.

name: Liceaga
description: Liceaga family. Passionate winemaking. Quality focused.

name: Mogor Badán
description: Historic family estate. One of Valle's pioneers.

name: Vinisterra
description: Wines of the Earth. Terroir-focused philosophy.

name: Clos de Tres Cantos
description: Artistic boutique winery. Creative expression in wine.

name: Lomita Wine Bar
description: Casual wine bar at Hacienda la Lomita. Relaxed tastings.

name: Tintos del Norte
description: Reds of the North. Bold red wine specialist.

name: Brancaia
description: Italian winery group's Mexican venture. Tuscan influence.

name: Viñedos Azteca
description: Aztec indigenous heritage. Pre-Hispanic winemaking traditions.

name: Natal Bosque
description: Experimental zero-kilometer forest kitchen. Chef Esteban's earlier project. By reservation.

name: Sol y Barro Estate
description: Sun and clay estate. Underground clay barrel aging.

name: Animalón
description: Michelin Star. Centuries-old oak tree. Contemporary Mexican. Javier Plascencia. Sommelier Award.

name: Damiana
description: Michelin Star. Chef Esteban Lluis. Daily changing tasting menu. Fresh local seasonal.

name: Conchas de Piedra
description: Michelin Star + Green Star. Chef Drew Deckman. Seafood specialist. Sparkling wine pairings.

name: Lunario
description: Michelin Star + Green Star. Chef Sheyla Alvarado. Changes with every new moon. Inspector's Best Dishes 2025.

name: Olivea Farm to Table
description: NEW Michelin Star + Green Star 2025. Own farms. Strong sustainability focus.

name: Deckman's en el Mogor
description: Green Star + Recommended. Chef Drew Deckman. Open-air kitchen. Sustainability champion.

name: Fauna
description: Michelin Recommended. At Bruma Wine Resort. Famous scallop dishes. Elegant service.

name: Restaurante Laja
description: Michelin Recommended. Chef Jair Téllez. Original Valle fine dining. Book weeks ahead.

name: Corazón de Tierra
description: Michelin Recommended. Chef Diego Hernández. Heart of Earth. Modern Mexican. Multi-course tastings.

name: Primitivo
description: Michelin Recommended. Chef Carolina Jiménez. 300-year oak. Fire pit cooking. Flourless chocolate cake with smoked lavender ice cream.

name: Misión 19
description: Michelin Recommended. Javier Plascencia. Baja Med cuisine pioneer. Tijuana location.

name: Tacos el Franc
description: Michelin Recommended + Bib Gourmand! Humble street stand. Authentic fish tacos. Cash only.

name: La Cocina de Doña Esthela
description: Bib Gourmand. Epic breakfast. Famous chilaquiles with scrambled eggs. Daily 7 AM-2 PM walk-ins.

name: Villa Torél
description: Bib Gourmand. At Santo Tomás winery. Historic setting. Excellent Mexican cuisine reasonable prices.

name: Casa Marcelo
description: Bib Gourmand. Ensenada seafood specialist. Fresh daily catches.

name: La Concheria
description: Bib Gourmand. Ensenada seafood. Shell specialist.

name: Humo y Sal
description: Bib Gourmand. Smoke and Salt. Fire-smoked cuisine Ensenada.

name: Finca Altozano
description: Farm-to-table with sweeping valley views. Excellent cuisine.

name: Troika Food Truck
description: Permanent at Vena Cava. Gourmet casual. Octopus tostadas. Roast suckling pig.

name: Fuego
description: At Corona Del Valle. Fire-grilled cuisine. One of our favorites.

name: Almatierra
description: Sustainable cuisine. Always amazing meal. Consistent quality.

name: Bruma Wine Garden
description: Casual section of Bruma Resort. Wine by glass. Bruma Market and Bakery on-site.

name: Adobe Guadalupe Food Truck
description: Spanish tapas in garden. Famous tongue/potato/shrimp dish.

name: Wendlandt Cervecería
description: Best Brewery Mexico 2x (2015). Award-winning IPAs. 150 gallons/week. Chef Krista Velasco pub menu.

name: Cerveza Cardera
description: Innovative Mexican-inspired flavors. Mango chamoy Berliner-Weisse. Hibiscus saison.

name: AguaMala
description: Shipping container brewery. Industrial chic. Rotating taps. Food truck partnerships.

name: Cervecería Transpeninsular
description: Baja California-inspired brews. Local ingredients. Highway 1 theme.

name: Lucky Irish Beer Garden
description: Irish-Mexican fusion beers. Beer garden atmosphere. Live music weekends.

name: Cerveza Bruer
description: Belgian-inspired ales. Farmhouse saisons. Sour specialists.

name: Sin Fronteras
description: Without Borders. Border culture celebration. Cross-cultural brews.

name: Heisenberg Tap Room
description: Science-themed brewery. Chemistry beers. Breaking Bad inspired.

name: El Chivo Gruñón
description: The Grumpy Goat. Traditional Mexican beer styles. Bohemian lagers.

name: Yopetas
description: Local favorite hangout. Rotating taps. Community vibe.

name: Calexico Brewing
description: Border brewery. Calexico-Mexicali fusion. Cross-border collaboration.

name: Colectivo Cervecero
description: Brewery collective. Cooperative model. Multiple brewers shared space.

name: Farland Aleworks
description: Experimental ales. Barrel-aging program. Limited releases.

name: Insurgente
description: Revolutionary craft brewery. Tijuana pioneer. Award-winning beers. Distribution throughout Baja.

name: Border Psycho
description: Extreme craft beers. High ABV. Experimental hops. Border culture celebration.
